ŠIN MEMORY OF SAM AND MAY BLACKHAM
Rednited in this place they loved.
where they shared many happy memories.
Loved and missed very much
by their daughters. Dawn and Lynn
ENJOY THIS PLACE"├
└[Left]
Maurice William Kings (Bill)
28/01/1933 - 27/02/1991
who enjoyed visiting Padstow during
his short retirement
and will always be missed by his
Family & Friends

[Right]
BRENDA MARY KINGS (BREN)
03/09/1936 - 28/03/2010
Beloved wife of Bill
who will always be
missed by Sam, Max
and family and friends"╩
ŪThis seat is erected to the
memory of Cecil Harvey and his wife
Mildred (nee Hawken)
who enjoyed this lovely area
May all who pass this way and rest
awhile also enjoy its tranquility
and beauty"╬
╦[Left]
With fond memories of
MARTIN COOK
His guitar is silent 
His fingers no longer work
Those days have slipped away
All the hours that he played
Just a man who played his guitar.

[Center]
WITH HAPPY MEMORIES
JOYCE AND GERALD (GUS) STEELS
OF LOUGHTON, ESSEX
WHO LOVED PADSTOW AND
REGARDED IT AS THEIR SECOND HOME

[RIGHT]
In loving memory of
JOHN and EILEEN PEARCE
from Epsom, Surrey
who spent so many happy times
in and around Padstow"Ó
▌HARRY EVANS
29/6/28 - 25/6/98
RETIRED FIRE OFFICER FROM SURREY WHO HELPED
CLEAR THE BEACHES OF HIS BELOVED CORNWALL
AFTER THE TORREY CANYON DISASTER 1967
DEARLY LOVED HUSBAND OF SYLVIA
FOREVER IN MY HEART
